AGI - It seemed a suicide but it was not.&nbsp;Giada Zanola>&nbsp; it did not voluntarily throw away from the highway's embosss; but it was killed by the comrade, who made her crash on the road. The body was found at the dawn of yesterday on the A4. The 34-year-old was thrown from the bridge, falling from about 15 meters.
&nbsp;
The turning point, of what initially seemed a suicide, arrived in the night, at the end of the investigations of the agents of the Polstrada of Padua and Venice and the Mobile Team of the Questura of Padua. Giada's partner was stopped for voluntary murder. &nbsp;
<h2> The lite
The woman at the height of a quarrel with her partner, was on the overpass and would have been rushed to the highway below, where at first was avoided by some cars in transit, and then be turned by a truck.&nbsp; Here the companion has precipitated it.&nbsp;Reconstructing the previous hours the agents have found elements that could lead to the&nbsp;<b> death of the woman&nbsp;</b>ad a homicide hypothesis.&nbsp;
<div </div
Investigators began to deepen in the &nbsp; You also encounter inconsistencies in the reconstruction of the last hours before the fact and yesterday, the man collapsed during the confrontation with the agents beginning to make partial admissions.
&nbsp;
Asked by the pm, he has reconstructed &nbsp;<b> the last hours:</b>&nbsp; he has spoken of his state of discomfort for the &nbsp;<b>relation now in crisis</b>; his concern of &nbsp;<b> no longer be able to see the son</b>&nbsp;starred with the partner; He spoke of the night between 28 and 29 May, when between the two a quarrel went on the highway overpass which is just less than a kilometre from the house of the coupleErano 3:30 at night of 29 May when the two were there, 15 meters above the three lanes of the A4, where&nbsp; the 34-year-old was thrown into the void before being hit by the means of passage.
&nbsp;
<h2>Zaia, blood chain that we must stop
"We must say it firmly, teaching it to all, from children to adults: violence on women is a horrible crime. We are facing a chain of blood that we do not and do not want to consider endless. Again we are faced with the shocking news of a woman, a young mother, who in a circumstance that could seem like a suicide would be, instead, killed by the comrade who has already been stopped with the charge of voluntary murder. If confirmed, we are again confronted with a disturbing death that once again raises deep questions and imposes us to maintain a high social reflection that surpasses the news and prevents us from getting used to the raw reality of similar tragedies. I express the sentiments of closeness to family, friends and friends in this suffering, in particular I think of the little three-year-old son who lost his mother and, in fact, the family." This is the comment of the President of the Veneto Region, Luca Zaia, on the news of the developments of the investigations on the death of the thirty-four-year-old Giada Zanola, who died after the fall from a overpass near Padua.
&nbsp;
"With the death of Giada the Veneto is again mourning >- the Governor continues - as in the days of Giulia, Vanessa, Sara and others even before them. It could be the fourth feminist only in a few months on horseback between last year and this; an unacceptable accounting that makes the skin happen and indignate. In the face of such a spiral of violence, we all have the duty to react with a resolute response that begins from the conviction that the culture of respect begins with not turning on the other side in the face of conditions of mistreatment and violence that you are aware of. Each reporting situations of this kind can save a life and support the antiviolence networks engaged in the fight against this plague that we cannot accept and must eradicate."
&nbsp;

