AGI -&nbsp;Separation of careers, reform of the Csm, institution of a High disciplinary Court for ordinary judiciary, requiring and judging. These are the central points of the constitutional reform ddl, composed of 8 articles, approved today by the Council of Ministers and defined by the Guardasigilli Carlo Nordio as an "historical trial".
&nbsp;
In the text it is specified that "the laws on the Higher Council of judiciary, judiciary and disciplinary jurisdiction are adequate to the provisions of this constitutional law within a year of its entry into force".&nbsp;These, in detail, the novelties of the reform.
&nbsp;
SECTION OF CARRIERS
&nbsp;
The first and second article of the ddl stipulates that in Article 87, tenth paragraph, of the Constitution, after the words "of the judiciary" the following "judicant and the Higher Council of the requiring judiciary" are added and that in the first paragraph of Article 102 of the Constitution, after the words "judiciary order" the distinguished careers of judgent and demanding magistrates are added. As regards Article 3 of the reform, it introduces amendments to Article 104 of the Constitution: "The judiciary is an independent and independent order of all other powers and is composed of judgement and career judges."
&nbsp;
DUE CSM PRESIED BY STATE CHAPTER
&nbsp;
Article 3 of the Decree also provides, always changing the provisions of the current Article 104 of the Constitution, that "the Higher Council of judiciary and the Higher Council of the required judiciary are chaired by the President of the Republic. The first President and the Attorney General of the Court of Cassation are entitled, respectively." The other components, on the other hand, "are extracted by lot, for a third party, from a list of ordinary professors of university in legal matters and lawyers after fifteen years of exercise, that the Parliament in common session, within six months of the settlement, compiled by election, and, for two thirds, respectively, between judiciary magistrates and the required magistrates, in the number and according to the procedures provided for by law". Each Council " elects its Vice-President among the members drawn up by the list compiled by Parliament - reads again in the text - and the members designated by draw last four years and cannot participate in the next draw procedure. They cannot, as long as they are in office, be enrolled in professional bodies, or be part of Parliament or a regional council." &nbsp;
&nbsp;
_
&nbsp;
Article 4 of the Decree amends Article 105 of the Constitution, establishing that "specifies each Higher Council of the judiciary, in accordance with the rules of the judiciary, the assumptions of assignments, transfers, evaluations of professionalism and the conferments of functions with regard to magistrates". The disciplinary jurisdiction with regard to ordinary magistrates, judging and requiring, is instead attributed to the High Court of disciplinary, consisting of fifteen judges, "three of which are appointed by the President of the Republic among ordinary professors of university in legal matters and lawyers with at least twenty years of exercise and three extracts from a list of subjects in possession of the same requirements that the Parliament in common session, within six months of the settlement, compiled by non-election The High Court, still provides for the reform, " elects the president among the judges appointed by the President of the Republic and those drawn up by the list compiled by Parliament. The judges of the High Court last four years and their assignment cannot be renewed. The High Court's Judgement Office is incompatible with that of a Member of Parliament, of the European Parliament, of a Regional Council or of the Government, with the exercise of the profession of lawyer and with any other office and office indicated by the law. Against the judgments issued by the High Court in the first instance, appeal shall be made, even for reasons of merit, only before the High Court itself, which judges without the participation of the members who have contested to pronounce the contested decision". &nbsp;
&nbsp;
<div </div
<h2>L'Anm: a defeat, damages citizens, ready for an important mobilization
"Today is a defeat for justice, it means giving more power to the political majority of turn, damaging first of all citizens," writes the Joint of the Anm.&nbsp;To take on new initiatives and to start an important mobilization, even from the territories, we decided to convene a Central Committee of urgency that will be held on June 15th," continues the note.&nbsp;
<h2>Nordio, "pm remains absolutely independent"></h2>
"The pm remains absolutely independent from the executive power, will enjoy the same guarantees of independence of the judges." This was said by Justice Minister Carlo Nordio, at a press conference after the Cdm, who approved the constitutional ddl on career separation. Commenting on the urgent call of the Am Junta, the Guardasigilli added: "The speech with the Anm is always open, the criticisms are the hall of democracy, we accept proposals, but also they must accept that the popular will is sacred and has been expressed by the voters who have sent us to do this reform." &nbsp;And again: "The Palamara scandal and others excited various protests, but the remedies were not prepared for current degeneration." For this reason, Nordio explained, "interrupting the link between voter and elected was our main task: the draw will not be between passers-by in the street but among people absolutely qualified".
<br The reform of the &nbsp;Giustizia&nbsp; approved today in Cdm - he then concluded Nordio - is "a tribute to Giovanni Falcone, who was favorable to the separation of careers, and to Giuliano Vassalli, hero of the Resistance, who wanted that code of which this reform had to be complied with". &nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<h2>Mantovano, "the text of the reform is not armored"></h2>
The text of the reform of Justice approved by the Council of Ministers "is not armored", said at the press conference the undersecretary to the Presidency of the Council, Alfredo Mantovano, who added: "I would not assume that you will be able to reach the referendum, in the sense - it has explained - that if it is valid the adherence to the substance that is proposed by the government and if there will be a comparison in Parliament in the merit, as we hope, on an unarmed text, open to the contribution of the entire Parliament, it is not so sure that you will arrive to the referendum. Let's take a step at a time," he explained, explaining the principles of the reform text. "The Council of Ministers approved the constitutional reform of the judiciary, in particular on the separation of careers, on the double Csm and on the High Court of Justice disciplinary proposed by the Minister Nordio, whom I thank on behalf of the whole government together with his staff and the entire ministry for the work carried out," Mantua began. "Being a demanding reform there was a work done until the last in the confrontation between the political forces of the majority until the last," he added.
&nbsp;
The time in Parliament for the reform of the &B; justice? They are those "required from the deepening of a matter that does not require political choices from the government and the majority, because the contents are entirely consistent with the commitments made before the voters but which I imagine will not be very rapid. But I hope they are not even dilated," Mantovano replied to the chroniclers.
&nbsp;
<h2> Penalisti, "reform ok, il&nbsp;Governo la port a fulfillment" ></h2>
"We hope that the Government, assumed the responsibility of this new text, will consistently carry out a reform that the criminal appeal has always considered essential to guarantee citizens a third judge, in implementation of the just process desired by our Constitution." Francesco Petrelli, president of the Union of Italian Penal Chambers, commented on the approval in Cdm of the reform on the separation of careers in judiciary. "The government text - notes the leader of the criminals - to a first reading appears in accordance with expectations in what follows the fundamental lines of our proposed constitutional reform of popular initiative of 2017. We have always considered perfect the constitutional reform of careers, aware of the importance of this intervention, so it is a question of carefully evaluating this new design." According to Petrelli, "two Councils chaired by the President of the Republic are guarantee of effective separation and at the same time of absolute autonomy and internal and external independence of Public Ministries and Judges". &nbsp;
